                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–2551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1019. Eyes only Gross. Dept this afternoon informed Brit Emb that you have been
                    requested to make discreet approach to Malik for purpose of eliciting
                    clarification re latter’s statement June 23.</p>
                <p>Dept accedes to Brit desire that you and Jebb see Malik together.</p>
                <p>You may wish to inform Jebb re the questions which you expect to raise with
                    Malik.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> we informed Brit Emb that Emb Moscow has
                    been asked to see Vyshinsky or Gromyko on same subject matter and ask same
                    questions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
